<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb86114dd-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s5391"><num value="5391">§ 5391.</num><heading> Definitions</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">For the purposes of this subchapter, “agency”, “employee”, and “position” have the meanings given them by section 5102.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb86114de-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/101/509/tV/s529/tI/s105/a/1">Pub. L. 101–509, title V, § 529 [title I, § 105(a)(1)]</ref>, <date date="1990-11-05">Nov. 5, 1990</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/104/1427">104 Stat. 1427</ref>, 1447.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idb86114df-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idb86114e0-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="idb86114e1-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective on such date as the President shall determine, but not earlier than 90 days, and not later than 180 days, after <date date="1990-11-05">Nov. 5, 1990</date>, see section 529 [title III, § 305] of <ref href="/us/pl/101/509">Pub. L. 101–509</ref>, set out as an Effective Date of 1990 Amendment note under <ref href="/us/usc/t5/s5301">section 5301 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
